Rating: 3
This is an excellent recipe. I followed the recipe exactly, and it turned out just right. We love eating it for breakfast. I was worried that it would be too much "pudding" like from its name, but although it is moist, it is more cake like, a little like a buckle cake. We liked it so much that I doubled the recipe the second time I made it. I will certainly make this again, as long as rhubarb and strawberries are in season.

Rating: 3
A great-tasting recipe that's no problem to make. Good for spring, since it doesn't have the heaviness that some crisps or crumbles do. I opted for a wooden spoon instead of the electric mixer and I don't think there was any difference. This recipe also lends itself to adding extra layers of flavour: you can replace the water for the rhubarb with brandy, although you might want to add a splash more than 2 tbsp.; add a hint of ginger, in either ground form in the pudding or in stem form in with the rhubarb; and/or sprinkle the top with sugar to give it a bit more texture when it's done. This would also be killer served with strawberry ice cream.